There's not even a non-veg dish. Look.

255
00:15:19,820 --> 00:15:21,970
You can't blame your mom.

256
00:15:21,970 --> 00:15:23,820
Fish induces heat. Meat induces phlegm.

257
00:15:23,820 --> 00:15:25,840
Vegetables keep you safe.

258
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:28,040
In your current condition,

259
00:15:28,040 --> 00:15:30,390
having whole-veg meals is the safest.

260
00:15:30,390 --> 00:15:31,550
It's easier said than done.

261
00:15:31,550 --> 00:15:33,720
You ate duck neck secretly. What do you have to say about that?

262
00:15:33,720 --> 00:15:36,510
I'm a man. How can I have vegetables only?

263
00:15:36,510 --> 00:15:38,871
Besides, at midnight, I secretly... No.

264
00:15:38,871 --> 00:15:41,790
How can you blame me for seeing me eat something at midnight?

265
00:15:41,790 --> 00:15:45,350
Well, I had to rummage around for something to eat.

266
00:15:45,350 --> 00:15:49,900
Why can't you have a meat-free meal?

267
00:15:53,770 --> 00:15:55,530
Let me tell you.

268
00:15:55,530 --> 00:15:57,960
Don't tell your mom about it.

269
00:15:57,960 --> 00:15:59,680
If you do,

270
00:15:59,680 --> 00:16:01,380
<i>[Yellow croaker]</i>
I won't get any pocket money in my next life.

271
00:16:01,380 --> 00:16:03,720
You're really something.

272
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:06,310
- Thank you.
- Eat it quickly.

273
00:16:10,390 --> 00:16:12,190
Have some rice.

274
00:16:12,190 --> 00:16:14,200
I'll finish the meat first.

275
00:16:16,590 --> 00:16:18,510
Hurry up. Don't dawdle!

276
00:16:18,510 --> 00:16:19,670
I'm walking.

277
00:16:19,670 --> 00:16:21,870
- Hurry up.
- Dongge.

278
00:16:22,480 --> 00:16:25,020
I brought this brat to apologize to you.

279
00:16:25,020 --> 00:16:28,020
Well, this spoiled brat took my expired cosmetics

280
00:16:28,020 --> 00:16:29,770
and gave them to Xue.

281
00:16:29,770 --> 00:16:32,320
I'm going to disown him.

282
00:16:32,320 --> 00:16:35,740
Hit or scold him? Do as you wish.

283
00:16:35,740 --> 00:16:39,260
Ms. Yu, sorry.

284
00:16:43,460 --> 00:16:44,750
Zhang Qi!

285
00:16:44,750 --> 00:16:46,240
What a spoiled brat.

286
00:16:46,240 --> 00:16:49,290
You've caused Xue to be disfigured.

287
00:16:49,290 --> 00:16:50,870
She... She's disfigured?

288
00:16:50,870 --> 00:16:54,070
Yes. Go and take a look yourself.

289
00:16:55,230 --> 00:16:57,070
Go on.

290
00:16:57,070 --> 00:16:59,470
I don't dare to.

291
00:17:07,680 --> 00:17:09,780
Xue.

292
00:17:11,240 --> 00:17:13,173
Xue.

293
00:17:25,660 --> 00:17:27,160
Is it so serious?

294
00:17:27,160 --> 00:17:29,800
Zhang Qi, give my face back to me!

295
00:17:29,800 --> 00:17:32,350
I didn't know that cosmetics had expiry dates.

296
00:17:32,350 --> 00:17:35,100
You've caused me so much harm. How dare you dodge!

297
00:17:35,690 --> 00:17:37,240
How do you want to vent out your anger?

298
00:17:37,240 --> 00:17:39,940
Hit me then. As long as it can please you.

299
00:17:51,540 --> 00:17:53,140
Not going to hit me?

300
00:18:00,080 --> 00:18:02,440
You tricked me?

301
00:18:02,440 --> 00:18:03,880
So what?

302
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:06,000
This is rather serious.

303
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,820
Do you wish that I was disfigured?

304
00:18:07,820 --> 00:18:09,350
You scared me to death.

305
00:18:09,350 --> 00:18:11,150
Let me have a look.

306
00:18:12,810 --> 00:18:14,750
It does look a little red.

307
00:18:14,750 --> 00:18:16,440
But it's better than I thought.

308
00:18:16,440 --> 00:18:17,920
What do you mean?

309
00:18:17,920 --> 00:18:20,140
It's itchy and painful. I can't touch it. I can't even have meat.

310
00:18:20,140 --> 00:18:23,431
I'm warning you. Don't irritate me these few days.

311
00:18:23,970 --> 00:18:26,660
Tell me.

312
00:18:30,640 --> 00:18:33,820
Well, be my errand boy for a week.

313
00:18:35,830 --> 00:18:38,350
What? You don't want to?

314
00:18:38,350 --> 00:18:41,250
Okay. You call the shots.

315
00:18:43,110 --> 00:18:44,140
That's more like it.

316
00:18:44,140 --> 00:18:46,400
Come on, massage me.

317
00:18:50,300 --> 00:18:51,933
Hurry up.

318
00:18:52,340 --> 00:18:54,210
Gentle.

319
00:18:56,920 --> 00:18:58,720
Apply more pressure.

320
00:19:03,170 --> 00:19:05,740
Luckily, your face is fine.

321
00:19:05,740 --> 00:19:09,500
If something were to happen to your face, what should you do?

322
00:19:09,500 --> 00:19:11,990
You're already rather ugly.

323
00:19:11,990 --> 00:19:13,930
What are you saying?

324
00:19:13,930 --> 00:19:16,470
I'm saying that even if something were to happen to your face,

325
00:19:16,470 --> 00:19:17,990
it wouldn't be a big deal.

326
00:19:17,990 --> 00:19:20,260
From now on, your meals are on me.

327
00:19:20,260 --> 00:19:21,170
Do you really mean it?

328
00:19:21,170 --> 00:19:22,790
Of course.

329
00:19:22,790 --> 00:19:26,510
Great. Then, I want to eat at Quanjude, Bianyifang,

330
00:19:26,510 --> 00:19:28,400
Dadong, and Siji Minfu.

331
00:19:28,400 --> 00:19:30,260
Those with duck meat specialties?

332
00:19:30,260 --> 00:19:31,680
Can you spare the ducks?

333
00:19:31,680 --> 00:19:33,790
What? You don't want to?

334
00:19:33,790 --> 00:19:36,750
I'm okay with it. Let's go there one by one.

335
00:19:36,750 --> 00:19:38,420
Carry on.

336
00:19:38,950 --> 00:19:40,930
<i>[Outpatient Clinic]</i>

337
00:19:40,930 --> 00:19:44,600
Doctor, why did it become worse? The skin is dry and itchy.

338
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:46,960
Look. There are even fine lines.

339
00:19:46,960 --> 00:19:48,340
I won't have wrinkles, will I?

340
00:19:48,340 --> 00:19:50,650
Having wrinkles is a small case.

341
00:19:50,650 --> 00:19:54,550
But it's a rather slow recovery.

342
00:19:55,160 --> 00:19:57,400
Did you eat things that you shouldn't?

343
00:19:57,400 --> 00:20:00,840
She didn't. We didn't allow her to do that.

344
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:06,000
She must have eaten something secretly.

345
00:20:07,970 --> 00:20:09,210
What's going on?

346
00:20:09,210 --> 00:20:11,440
Did you give her something behind my back?

347
00:20:11,440 --> 00:20:14,280
No. It's...

348
00:20:14,280 --> 00:20:18,890
That day, she ate some fish.

349
00:20:18,890 --> 00:20:21,900
See? She can't have seafood.

350
00:20:21,900 --> 00:20:23,490
Fine.

351
00:20:23,490 --> 00:20:25,720
You take care of her.

352
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:30,000
Doctor, we'll keep her on the diet.

353
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:30,931
- Mom!
- Come on.

354
00:20:30,931 --> 00:20:33,070
Abide by my requirement, okay?

355
00:20:33,630 --> 00:20:34,880
Well, it's late. Don't cook.

356
00:20:34,880 --> 00:20:37,310
Let's eat out. My treat.

357
00:20:37,310 --> 00:20:39,411
Eat? All you know is eating.

358
00:20:39,411 --> 00:20:41,671
The young one is ignorant. The old plays a fool, too.

359
00:20:41,671 --> 00:20:43,350
It has been so many days. She couldn't go to school or meet anyone.

360
00:20:43,350 --> 00:20:45,410
Don't you feel anxious?

361
00:20:50,300 --> 00:20:51,820
Don't hit her so hard.

362
00:20:51,820 --> 00:20:53,720
Will she remember it then?

363
00:20:53,720 --> 00:20:55,940
Don't scratch!

364
00:20:55,940 --> 00:20:57,880
When kids from other families get hurt,

365
00:20:57,880 --> 00:20:59,450
their moms are so worried about them.

366
00:20:59,450 --> 00:21:02,500
All you wanted was for me to remember it.

367
00:21:05,060 --> 00:21:06,200
Stop crying.

368
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:07,610
Tears irritate the skin.

369
00:21:07,610 --> 00:21:09,110
I won't stop!

370
00:21:09,110 --> 00:21:11,650
It has been so many days. You didn't say anything pleasant to the ear at all.

371
00:21:11,650 --> 00:21:13,540
You threw my stuff away. You forbade me to have meat.

372
00:21:13,540 --> 00:21:15,770
Can't I cry now?

373
00:21:15,770 --> 00:21:18,000
Why are you yelling at me? Why are you yelling?

374
00:21:18,000 --> 00:21:19,960
Did I cause the allergy? Did I cause it?

375
00:21:19,960 --> 00:21:22,790
You're so fierce. I don't want to see you again!

376
00:21:22,790 --> 00:21:24,790
Where are you going?

377
00:21:24,790 --> 00:21:26,450
Follow her.

378
00:21:26,450 --> 00:21:29,790
She's hurt. She'll be all right after crying.

379
00:21:29,790 --> 00:21:31,410
Then, come home with me now.

380
00:21:31,410 --> 00:21:32,510
Why?

381
00:21:32,510 --> 00:21:36,500
Help me prepare her favorite food.

382
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:38,050
Geez.

383
00:21:38,050 --> 00:21:42,960
<i>[Wenrentang Pharmacy]</i>

384
00:21:44,600 --> 00:21:45,920
Sunian.

385
00:21:45,920 --> 00:21:50,070
<i>[Sales Counter]</i>

386
00:22:06,610 --> 00:22:08,343
Stop crying.

387
00:22:08,343 --> 00:22:11,210
Tears hurt the skin.

388
00:22:14,650 --> 00:22:16,820
It hurts.

389
00:22:23,400 --> 00:22:25,750
Take off your mask. Let me have a look.

390
00:22:27,310 --> 00:22:28,843
It's ugly.

391
00:22:29,610 --> 00:22:31,140
I've seen it all.

392
00:22:31,140 --> 00:22:32,890
Even your sniveling look during childhood.

393
00:22:32,890 --> 00:22:34,890
But I still played with you, didn't I?

394
00:22:36,170 --> 00:22:37,870
It's a hot summer.

395
00:22:37,870 --> 00:22:40,780
Won't the mask make it worse?

396
00:22:47,300 --> 00:22:50,433
Tell me. Why are you crying?

397
00:22:51,450 --> 00:22:53,350
What do you think?

398
00:22:53,350 --> 00:22:55,020
I failed in becoming an interpreter.

399
00:22:55,020 --> 00:22:57,310
I was disfigured. And my mom keeps scolding me.

400
00:22:57,310 --> 00:22:59,770
- What is the main reason?
- The interpreter thing of course.

401
00:23:01,980 --> 00:23:04,350
I was looking forward to it.

402
00:23:04,350 --> 00:23:06,570
The entire alley knew about it.

403
00:23:06,570 --> 00:23:10,580
I couldn't do it at last. So shameful.

404
00:23:12,350 --> 00:23:14,000
There's nothing to feel ashamed of.

405
00:23:14,000 --> 00:23:18,910
After a week, I guarantee that everyone won't remember it.

406
00:23:18,910 --> 00:23:21,380
Others might forget it,

407
00:23:21,380 --> 00:23:23,340
but not the teacher, I'm afraid.

408
00:23:23,340 --> 00:23:26,110
Then, I can kiss the opportunity to study abroad goodbye.

409
00:23:26,110 --> 00:23:28,260
Opportunity comes to those who are prepared.

410
00:23:28,260 --> 00:23:31,630
You didn't manage to be the interpreter, but you've worked so hard for it.

411
00:23:31,630 --> 00:23:33,350
Your efforts won't be in vain.

412
00:23:33,350 --> 00:23:36,710
You just need a chance to practice.

413
00:23:36,710 --> 00:23:39,820
Moreover, if you want to practice speaking,

414
00:23:39,820 --> 00:23:41,850
my mom can help you.

415
00:23:49,170 --> 00:23:54,850
Then, what about my face?

416
00:23:54,850 --> 00:23:59,310
If my face doesn't recover, I'm afraid

417
00:23:59,310 --> 00:24:02,300
no one will want me anymore.

418
00:24:04,680 --> 00:24:06,550
How old are you now?

419
00:24:06,550 --> 00:24:09,070
Why are you so concerned about such a thing?

420
00:24:09,070 --> 00:24:11,370
You're worried that you can't get married?

421
00:24:17,750 --> 00:24:19,383
All right.

422
00:24:22,410 --> 00:24:26,690
If that day comes, I'll marry you.

423
00:24:33,890 --> 00:24:36,480
If you can't get married,

424
00:24:39,650 --> 00:24:41,283
I'll marry you.

425
00:24:41,830 --> 00:24:43,363
All right?

426
00:24:46,240 --> 00:24:48,090
I think it's all right.

427
00:24:51,640 --> 00:24:54,250
Come on.

428
00:24:57,550 --> 00:24:59,283
Thank you, Boss.

429
00:24:59,283 --> 00:25:01,090
The tissue is on your credit.

430
00:25:21,880 --> 00:25:25,380
Hi, lad. What are you looking for? Do you need any help?

431
00:25:27,020 --> 00:25:28,640
These are cosmetics for girls.

432
00:25:28,640 --> 00:25:31,090
Are you getting a gift?

433
00:25:31,090 --> 00:25:32,170
Yes.

434
00:25:32,170 --> 00:25:33,580
How old is she?

435
00:25:33,580 --> 00:25:34,780
A high school student.

436
00:25:34,780 --> 00:25:37,480
I know it then.

437
00:25:37,480 --> 00:25:38,610
What about this?

438
00:25:38,610 --> 00:25:41,450
It's pink and tender. It suits teenage girls well.

439
00:25:47,610 --> 00:25:49,540
Okay. Thank you.

440
00:25:49,540 --> 00:25:50,820
What about a bottle of perfume?

441
00:25:50,820 --> 00:25:53,470
This is called the Taste of First Love.

442
00:25:55,240 --> 00:25:57,400
No, thanks.

443
00:25:58,610 --> 00:26:00,440
He's shy.

444
00:26:00,440 --> 00:26:03,340
Mom, you suddenly brought me to the mall.

445
00:26:03,340 --> 00:26:04,850
You didn't bring Dad along.

446
00:26:04,850 --> 00:26:06,780
You're not selling me off, are you?

447
00:26:06,780 --> 00:26:07,920
Selling you off?

448
00:26:07,920 --> 00:26:09,500
I have to pay the difference if that were so.

449
00:26:09,500 --> 00:26:11,600
Then, why are we here?

450
00:26:11,600 --> 00:26:14,030
Shopping, of course.

451
00:26:14,980 --> 00:26:16,690
Shopping? You're so stingy.

452
00:26:16,690 --> 00:26:17,850
What did you say?

453
00:26:17,850 --> 00:26:19,170
Huh? What do we buy?

454
00:26:19,170 --> 00:26:21,070
What do you think?

455
00:26:23,440 --> 00:26:25,520
Sunian, why are you here?

456
00:26:25,520 --> 00:26:28,310
I came to get something for my mom.

457
00:26:28,310 --> 00:26:29,960
What did you buy?

458
00:26:31,440 --> 00:26:34,340
Hey, why are you so nosy?

459
00:26:34,880 --> 00:26:36,850
We'll get going.

460
00:26:37,680 --> 00:26:38,900
Bye, Mrs. Shao.

461
00:26:38,900 --> 00:26:40,980
Bye, Sunian.

462
00:26:44,820 --> 00:26:46,453
Mom!

463
00:26:46,453 --> 00:26:49,430
Why did you bring me to the cosmetic counters?

464
00:26:50,890 --> 00:26:53,420
I've never used these kinds of things.

465
00:26:53,420 --> 00:26:56,110
And you don't know how to use them.

466
00:26:56,110 --> 00:26:58,000
I've thought it through these few days.

467
00:26:58,000 --> 00:27:00,980
You've grown up. You'll be going to the university soon.

468
00:27:00,980 --> 00:27:03,130
It's normal to want to look beautiful.

469
00:27:03,130 --> 00:27:07,790
Instead of forbidding you to use them, it's better to buy you some good ones

470
00:27:07,790 --> 00:27:11,400
in case you do it recklessly and end up in the hospital again.

471
00:27:12,780 --> 00:27:14,613
Miss.

472
00:27:14,613 --> 00:27:15,590
Hi.

473
00:27:15,590 --> 00:27:19,740
Can you recommend something suitable for my daughter?

474
00:27:19,740 --> 00:27:22,450
What is your price range?

475
00:27:22,930 --> 00:27:24,500
The best.

476
00:27:24,500 --> 00:27:26,240
This is our latest series.

477
00:27:26,240 --> 00:27:28,450
It has good moisturizing and sun protection effects.

478
00:27:28,450 --> 00:27:30,740
Try it.

479
00:27:30,740 --> 00:27:32,750
Let my daughter try it then.

480
00:27:32,750 --> 00:27:35,100
Xue, come over.

481
00:27:36,070 --> 00:27:37,770
It's okay. Try it.

482
00:27:37,770 --> 00:27:40,590
This has a good sun protection effect.

483
00:27:42,070 --> 00:27:43,300
And it's moisturizing.

484
00:27:43,300 --> 00:27:45,780
It's very suitable for young girls like you.

485
00:27:45,780 --> 00:27:46,510
How is it?

486
00:27:46,510 --> 00:27:47,680
It has a good sun protection effect.

487
00:27:47,680 --> 00:27:50,980
- It's suitable for the outdoors.
- Really?

488
00:27:50,980 --> 00:27:53,300
It has a mild scent.

489
00:28:08,440 --> 00:28:10,210
I'm home.

490
00:28:10,210 --> 00:28:12,410
Sunian, you're home.

491
00:28:29,230 --> 00:28:31,070
What is this?

492
00:28:31,070 --> 00:28:32,763
For you.

493
00:28:33,400 --> 00:28:35,860
For me?

494
00:28:37,540 --> 00:28:40,440
It's not a festival or my birthday.

495
00:28:40,440 --> 00:28:43,310
Why did you get me a gift?

496
00:28:43,310 --> 00:28:47,210
I suddenly thought of it.

497
00:28:47,210 --> 00:28:49,900
So sweet.

498
00:29:01,720 --> 00:29:04,820
This seems to be...

499
00:29:04,820 --> 00:29:07,750
for girls.

500
00:29:11,440 --> 00:29:14,580
I just grabbed it.

501
00:29:14,580 --> 00:29:16,550
Just make do.

502
00:29:17,410 --> 00:29:21,440
Well, I think you didn't buy it for me,

503
00:29:21,440 --> 00:29:25,050
but for someone else

504
00:29:25,050 --> 00:29:27,330
and you didn't give it to her.

505
00:29:27,330 --> 00:29:28,440
I need to study.

506
00:29:28,440 --> 00:29:30,510
Hey! Tell me.

507
00:29:30,510 --> 00:29:33,600
I can help you with it.

508
00:29:33,600 --> 00:29:35,530
Do you need me to give it to her for you?

509
00:29:36,290 --> 00:29:38,980
<i>[Class 1 Grade 11]</i>

510
00:29:42,630 --> 00:29:44,400
<i>[Song of the Pipa by Bai Juyi]</i>

511
00:29:44,400 --> 00:29:47,000
Before we dismiss, I have something to tell you.

512
00:29:47,000 --> 00:29:49,030
The 10th-anniversary school celebration is around the corner.

513
00:29:49,030 --> 00:29:52,740
This time, the performance is going to be the grandest in history.

514
00:29:52,740 --> 00:29:55,330
If you're good at something, you can participate in it.

515
00:29:55,330 --> 00:29:58,960
Those who want to give a show may register with the entertainment committee.

516
00:30:00,370 --> 00:30:03,510
But it must not affect your studies.

517
00:30:03,510 --> 00:30:05,670
- Okay?
<i>- Okay.</i>

518
00:30:05,670 --> 00:30:07,590
Okay. Class dismissed.

519
00:30:08,310 --> 00:30:09,461
- Shiyin.
- Quick.

520
00:30:09,461 --> 00:30:10,630
Register it for me. A play.

521
00:30:10,630 --> 00:30:12,510
- What's the name?

522
00:30:12,510 --> 00:30:15,240
I haven't thought of it yet. Just write "Shao Xue's show".

523
00:30:15,240 --> 00:30:16,400
Quick. Write it down.

524
00:30:16,400 --> 00:30:18,133
Go on.

525
00:30:18,880 --> 00:30:20,920
- What's the show?
- A play.

526
00:30:20,920 --> 00:30:22,680
Amazing. What's the story?

527
00:30:22,680 --> 00:30:23,550
I haven't thought of the story yet.

528
00:30:23,550 --> 00:30:26,310
But the casts are in place, waiting for my instruction.

529
00:30:26,310 --> 00:30:27,350
I reject it.

530
00:30:27,350 --> 00:30:28,420
Why?

531
00:30:28,420 --> 00:30:30,990
<i>[Competition Class]</i>

532
00:30:30,990 --> 00:30:34,900
<i>[Keep Quiet]</i>

533
00:30:34,900 --> 00:30:38,210
I already feel tired studying every day. I don't have time to sleep.

534
00:30:38,210 --> 00:30:39,480
Where do I find the time to act in a play?

535
00:30:39,480 --> 00:30:41,510
Then, why did you help Qiaomu shoot a short film?

536
00:30:41,510 --> 00:30:42,680
Keep your voice down.

537
00:30:42,680 --> 00:30:44,160
I was forced into it.

538
00:30:44,160 --> 00:30:46,750
I'll be the director this time. Aren't you going to do it for my sake?

539
00:30:46,750 --> 00:30:48,730
You'll be the director?

540
00:30:48,730 --> 00:30:50,300
Are you looking down on me?

541
00:30:50,300 --> 00:30:51,500
I'll ask Sunian.

542
00:30:51,500 --> 00:30:52,680
He won't act.

543
00:30:52,680 --> 00:30:54,480
Sunian will definitely join.

544
00:30:54,480 --> 00:30:56,113
I reject.

545
00:30:56,880 --> 00:30:58,110
Why, Sunian?

546
00:30:58,110 --> 00:30:59,400
I don't want to act.

547
00:30:59,400 --> 00:31:01,130
You're so frank.

548
00:31:01,130 --> 00:31:03,340
You don't even give me a reason.

549
00:31:03,340 --> 00:31:07,620
Then, Grade 12 students are not allowed to participate.

550
00:31:07,620 --> 00:31:12,130
You're not allowed to register. It's not that you can't participate in other shows.

551
00:31:12,980 --> 00:31:14,860
Then...

552
00:31:16,550 --> 00:31:18,200
I just don't want to act.

553
00:31:18,200 --> 00:31:20,310
Told you.

554
00:31:22,410 --> 00:31:24,000
Can I reject?

555
00:31:24,000 --> 00:31:25,890
What's your reason?

556
00:31:25,890 --> 00:31:27,580
I have to work at the supermarket.

557
00:31:27,580 --> 00:31:29,630
So I don't have the time.

558
00:31:31,510 --> 00:31:35,170
Shiyin, I have been abandoned by the whole world.

559
00:31:35,170 --> 00:31:37,200
I only have you now.

560
00:31:37,200 --> 00:31:38,980
I can't act.

561
00:31:38,980 --> 00:31:41,000
What's your reason?

562
00:31:41,000 --> 00:31:44,060
I'm doing the opening dance. It's very important. I don't have the time.

563
00:31:44,060 --> 00:31:46,730
The audition hasn't started yet. Why are you doing the opening dance then?

564
00:31:46,730 --> 00:31:48,930
We're the school's dance troupe. We're exempted from the audition.

565
00:31:48,930 --> 00:31:51,180
What will you be dancing to then?

566
00:31:51,180 --> 00:31:53,780
Revelry of Doomsday.

567
00:31:53,780 --> 00:31:56,960
It's the school celebration. Why are you dancing to the Revelry of Doomsday?

568
00:31:56,960 --> 00:31:58,450
It sounds great, isn't it?

569
00:31:58,450 --> 00:32:00,880
Our choreographer has such a unique idea.

570
00:32:00,880 --> 00:32:05,310
He returned from overseas. Handsome and mesmerizing.

571
00:32:05,310 --> 00:32:06,440
Are you crazy?

572
00:32:06,440 --> 00:32:09,740
Didn't you order a song dedicated to Wang Haoran?

573
00:32:09,740 --> 00:32:11,490
Wang Haoran?

574
00:32:11,490 --> 00:32:12,830
Wang Haoran was just someone I liked on a whim.

575
00:32:12,830 --> 00:32:14,000
I've never spoken to him.

576
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:17,060
But I adore this teacher very much.

577
00:32:17,060 --> 00:32:20,460
If you'd seen the way he danced, you'd definitely be fascinated by him.

578
00:32:20,460 --> 00:32:22,240
Your enthusiasm only lasts three minutes.

579
00:32:22,240 --> 00:32:24,480
After the dance, you'll change your target.

580
00:32:24,480 --> 00:32:25,830
Join me in my play.

581
00:32:25,830 --> 00:32:28,490
Art is what will be everlasting.

582
00:32:29,400 --> 00:32:31,691
Am I a half-hearted person?

583
00:32:32,480 --> 00:32:35,110
Yes, you are!

584
00:32:37,720 --> 00:32:39,820
A bunch of traitors.

585
00:32:40,440 --> 00:32:43,480
Xue, don't be angry.

586
00:32:44,260 --> 00:32:46,450
I've been betrayed by the whole world!

587
00:32:46,450 --> 00:32:48,400
No one is willing to act in my play!

588
00:32:48,400 --> 00:32:52,000
I've registered and written half of the script!

589
00:32:53,690 --> 00:32:55,890
If you need someone,

590
00:32:55,890 --> 00:32:58,300
I...

591
00:32:58,300 --> 00:33:00,790
I can join.

592
00:33:02,550 --> 00:33:04,850
Really? Are you willing to act in it, really?

593
00:33:04,850 --> 00:33:07,000
If you are, whether the male lead, the female lead,

594
00:33:07,000 --> 00:33:09,200
the righteous party, or the villain, you can choose to play any role.

595
00:33:09,200 --> 00:33:12,100
Just give me a minor role.

596
00:33:12,100 --> 00:33:15,030
I'm... not presentable.

597
00:33:15,030 --> 00:33:16,200
What are you talking about?

598
00:33:16,200 --> 00:33:18,200
Look at your big eyes and high nose bridge.

599
00:33:18,200 --> 00:33:20,200
Under the light after applying some makeup, you'll look stunning.

600
00:33:20,200 --> 00:33:21,730
- Xue.
- What is it?

601
00:33:21,730 --> 00:33:23,100
What about... I'm talking to my female lead.

602
00:33:23,100 --> 00:33:26,280
- Actually, I can act...
- Aren't you going to dance to Doomsday or something?

603
00:33:26,280 --> 00:33:28,550
Go ahead!

604
00:33:28,550 --> 00:33:30,940
It's a deal then.

605
00:33:30,940 --> 00:33:33,600
I'll write the script now.

606
00:33:33,600 --> 00:33:35,240
Xue...

607
00:33:42,200 --> 00:33:44,800
Jin Ning and Zheng had a row?

608
00:33:45,900 --> 00:33:48,300
Impossible. We live next door.

609
00:33:48,300 --> 00:33:50,700
Why didn't we hear any noise?

610
00:33:50,700 --> 00:33:52,400
Keep your voice down.

611
00:33:52,400 --> 00:33:55,000
Do they speak loudly like us?

612
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:56,600
I just noticed it.

613
00:33:56,600 --> 00:34:00,600
The two crossed each other without speaking a word.

614
00:34:00,600 --> 00:34:02,700
I don't believe they'd have a row.

615
00:34:02,700 --> 00:34:03,400
Look.

616
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:05,100
I've known Jin Ning for over a decade.

617
00:34:05,100 --> 00:34:07,000
She has never spoken harshly.

618
00:34:07,000 --> 00:34:08,600
Jing Ning is the apple of Zheng's eyes.

619
00:34:08,600 --> 00:34:10,000
He loves her so much.

620
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:12,400
How could he have a row with her?

621
00:34:13,600 --> 00:34:14,600
Stop.

622
00:34:14,600 --> 00:34:16,900
Ms. Jin, getting some water?

623
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:40,000
Look. What did I tell you?

624
00:34:44,600 --> 00:34:47,200
<i>[One week ago]</i>

625
00:34:48,400 --> 00:34:51,000
<i>Jin Ning, dinner is ready.</i>

626
00:34:51,000 --> 00:34:53,300
<i>Wait a minute. I'll be right there.</i>

627
00:34:54,500 --> 00:34:56,800
<i>Let's have dinner first.</i>

628
00:35:00,710 --> 00:35:02,820
<i>[A few days later]</i>

629
00:35:18,800 --> 00:35:20,200
<i>You seldom eat on time.</i>

630
00:35:20,200 --> 00:35:21,600
<i>It's bad for your stomach.</i>

631
00:35:21,600 --> 00:35:23,200
<i>Let's have dinner first.</i>

632
00:35:23,200 --> 00:35:24,500
<i>It's the climax.</i>

633
00:35:24,500 --> 00:35:26,900
<i>Don't disturb me.</i>

634
00:35:38,800 --> 00:35:41,000
<i>[Just one day ago]</i>

635
00:35:43,200 --> 00:35:46,000
<i>Can you stop it for a while?</i>

636
00:35:47,800 --> 00:35:49,700
<i>It's almost over.</i>

637
00:35:53,000 --> 00:35:56,600
<i>Please. Can we have our dinner first?</i>

638
00:35:57,300 --> 00:35:58,600
<i>It's the climax.</i>

639
00:35:58,600 --> 00:36:02,600
<i>You always say so.</i>

640
00:36:15,300 --> 00:36:17,100
<i>Have dinner first.</i>

641
00:36:21,150 --> 00:36:24,380
<i>- Turn it on.
- No. Have dinner first.</i>

642
00:36:27,200 --> 00:36:29,500
<i>If you don't, I won't eat.</i>

643
00:36:29,500 --> 00:36:32,200
<i>You... Sunian!</i>

644
00:36:32,200 --> 00:36:34,200
<i>Look at your mom. She...</i>

645
00:36:34,200 --> 00:36:37,600
<i>- What have I done?
- You're being unreasonable.</i>

646
00:36:39,800 --> 00:36:41,400
<i>I...</i>

647
00:36:41,400 --> 00:36:43,600
<i>I'll check in the kitchen.</i>

648
00:36:49,800 --> 00:36:51,000
<i>Be good.</i>

649
00:36:51,000 --> 00:36:53,200
<i>Can we have dinner first?</i>

650
00:36:53,200 --> 00:36:56,000
<i>How could you reproach me in front of our son?</i>

651
00:36:56,000 --> 00:36:58,400
<i>He was just right here.</i>

652
00:36:59,600 --> 00:37:00,800
<i>Apologize.</i>

653
00:37:00,800 --> 00:37:03,700
<i>You're the unreasonable one and I need to apologize?</i>

654
00:37:03,700 --> 00:37:05,600
<i>Why should I?</i>

655
00:37:08,400 --> 00:37:10,600
<i>You've changed.</i>

656
00:37:19,500 --> 00:37:21,800
<i>Aren't you going to console her?</i>

657
00:37:21,800 --> 00:37:23,300
<i>No.</i>

658
00:37:23,300 --> 00:37:26,000
<i>It's time to cure your mom's bad habit.</i>

659
00:37:29,200 --> 00:37:31,600
<i>You have my admiration.</i>

660
00:37:31,600 --> 00:37:35,200
It was a matter of having dinner or watching television.

661
00:37:36,200 --> 00:37:38,400
What was there to argue about?

662
00:37:38,400 --> 00:37:39,600
Dinner's ready.

663
00:37:39,600 --> 00:37:41,900
We should eat when it's time for dinner.

664
00:37:41,900 --> 00:37:43,600
Why must she watch the television?

665
00:37:43,600 --> 00:37:45,600
Couldn't she watch it after dinner?

666
00:37:45,600 --> 00:37:48,600
No wonder you can't find a girlfriend.

667
00:37:48,600 --> 00:37:51,400
You need to go along with women.

668
00:37:54,670 --> 00:37:57,480
You women are so troublesome.

669
00:38:04,800 --> 00:38:06,800
Xue, I'm leaving.

670
00:38:06,800 --> 00:38:09,600
I'll show you the completed script tomorrow.

671
00:38:10,700 --> 00:38:12,500
- I...
- What is it?

672
00:38:12,500 --> 00:38:14,900
I'm going to tailor-make a female lead role for you.

673
00:38:14,900 --> 00:38:17,500
You... You're indeed going to let me play the female lead?

674
00:38:17,500 --> 00:38:18,500
Of course.

675
00:38:18,500 --> 00:38:21,500
- I can't. I have stage fright.
- Stage fright?

676
00:38:21,500 --> 00:38:25,000
I feel nervous on stage and can't say a word.

677
00:38:25,000 --> 00:38:26,900
It's fine. I feel nervous on stage, too.

678
00:38:26,900 --> 00:38:28,200
Just practice more.

679
00:38:28,200 --> 00:38:31,000
Xue, I... I don't know how to put it.

680
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:32,900
But I'll embarrass you.

681
00:38:32,900 --> 00:38:34,000
It's better not to choose me.

682
00:38:34,000 --> 00:38:35,200
Sorry.

683
00:38:35,200 --> 00:38:36,800
Tang Ya!

684
00:38:46,600 --> 00:38:48,100
You're home.

685
00:38:49,400 --> 00:38:52,200
Dad, where's Mom?

686
00:38:53,400 --> 00:38:56,500
She's having dinner at Xue's home.

687
00:38:56,500 --> 00:38:58,200
She's still mad?

688
00:38:58,200 --> 00:39:01,400
It has gotten worse.

689
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:11,600
Jin Ning, eat up.

690
00:39:11,600 --> 00:39:13,400
Here. Try this smoked tofu.

691
00:39:13,400 --> 00:39:14,800
- Ms. Jin Ning.
- Thank you.

692
00:39:14,800 --> 00:39:17,000
Why did you have a row with Mr. Zheng?

693
00:39:17,000 --> 00:39:20,000
Xue, are you full?

694
00:39:20,000 --> 00:39:22,000
I haven't even started.

695
00:39:22,800 --> 00:39:28,500
No. We have different living habits.

696
00:39:28,500 --> 00:39:30,800
That's how life is. Having a racket.

697
00:39:30,800 --> 00:39:32,400
- That's the fun.
- That's right.

698
00:39:32,400 --> 00:39:34,400
Yes. Look at my mom and my dad.

699
00:39:34,400 --> 00:39:36,600
They have so much fun every day.

700
00:39:37,440 --> 00:39:39,200
Xue, we adults are talking.

701
00:39:39,200 --> 00:39:41,400
Why do you interrupt?

702
00:39:43,000 --> 00:39:43,900
Jin Ning is here.

703
00:39:43,900 --> 00:39:45,500
Don't lecture our girl at dinner time.

704
00:39:45,500 --> 00:39:47,100
Did I lecture her?

705
00:39:47,100 --> 00:39:49,400
You... You didn't reproach her. But you reproached me.

706
00:39:49,400 --> 00:39:52,600
No. You yelled at her. But you reproached me.

707
00:39:53,200 --> 00:39:55,100
Did I?

708
00:39:55,100 --> 00:39:56,900
Look, you deny it.

709
00:39:56,900 --> 00:39:58,200
This is the way I talk.

710
00:39:58,200 --> 00:39:59,800
Did I yell at her?

711
00:39:59,800 --> 00:40:01,300
Isn't that yelling?

712
00:40:01,300 --> 00:40:03,500
She barely came here for dinner. Yet you had to lecture our kid at the dinner table.

713
00:40:03,500 --> 00:40:05,900
I know what you're up to!

714
00:40:12,200 --> 00:40:15,400
Was class tiring today?

715
00:40:17,200 --> 00:40:19,100
No.

716
00:40:22,300 --> 00:40:24,700
Do you have a lot of homework?

717
00:40:27,400 --> 00:40:28,600
No.

718
00:40:30,400 --> 00:40:31,800
I...

719
00:40:32,800 --> 00:40:35,600
Is the food salty?

720
00:40:37,200 --> 00:40:40,200
Dad, don't force it.

721
00:40:45,200 --> 00:40:46,800
Sunian!

722
00:40:46,800 --> 00:40:48,500
- Mr. Zheng.
- Xue.

723
00:40:48,500 --> 00:40:49,800
You're still having dinner?

724
00:40:49,800 --> 00:40:50,900
Almost done.

725
00:40:50,900 --> 00:40:52,600
Have you had dinner? Join us. There's chicken.

726
00:40:52,600 --> 00:40:54,800
I already had dinner.

727
00:40:56,200 --> 00:40:58,500
Did Ms. Jin Ning eat well?

728
00:40:58,500 --> 00:41:00,100
Yes.

729
00:41:00,100 --> 00:41:02,200
That's good then.

730
00:41:02,200 --> 00:41:04,100
Dad, I'm full.

731
00:41:04,900 --> 00:41:06,400
- Let's go.
- We'll get going then.

732
00:41:06,400 --> 00:41:08,700
- Bye, Mr. Zheng.
- Bye.

733
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:37,600
"OLD SONG" - Featuring artist: Ma Di

734
00:41:37,600 --> 00:41:41,600
♫ <i>As I traverse this path without minding it</i> ♫

735
00:41:41,600 --> 00:41:45,100
♫ <i>My memory does all the hard work for me</i> ♫

736
00:41:45,100 --> 00:41:53,200
♫ <i>All the memories are embedded deep within my heart</i> ♫

737
00:41:53,200 --> 00:41:56,700
♫ <i>The past I've been hiding from year after year</i> ♫

738
00:41:56,700 --> 00:42:00,600
♫ <i>Carved into the days long gone</i> ♫

739
00:42:00,600 --> 00:42:08,400
♫ <i>Although simplicity is plain, its vibrancy has never faded</i> ♫

740
00:42:08,400 --> 00:42:12,200
♫ <i>Those songs in the past</i> ♫

741
00:42:12,200 --> 00:42:16,000
♫ <i>They had accompanied me through everything</i> ♫

742
00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:23,600
♫ <i>Singing about the stubbornness of our youth</i> ♫

743
00:42:23,600 --> 00:42:31,300
♫ <i>Using this song to boost our courage as we sing</i> ♫

744
00:42:31,300 --> 00:42:39,000
♫ <i>Please don't cry because you have me</i> ♫

745
00:42:55,600 --> 00:42:58,800
♫ <i>Until I saw the bustling city</i> ♫

746
00:42:58,800 --> 00:43:02,600
♫ <i>Until I realized that it was once within my reach</i> ♫

747
00:43:02,600 --> 00:43:10,200
♫ <i>I was this sober once but I still did the same thing</i> ♫

748
00:43:10,200 --> 00:43:14,100
♫ <i>As days go by, I wish to forget</i> ♫

749
00:43:14,100 --> 00:43:18,000
♫ <i>But unknowingly, I remember them again</i> ♫

750
00:43:18,000 --> 00:43:21,800
♫ <i>I remember the deep feelings that were long gone</i> ♫

751
00:43:21,800 --> 00:43:25,800
♫ <i>Within those simple days</i> ♫

752
00:43:25,800 --> 00:43:33,400
♫ <i>Those songs in the past, they had accompanied me</i> ♫

753
00:43:33,400 --> 00:43:41,200
♫ <i>As I regretted our parting during our youth</i> ♫

754
00:43:41,200 --> 00:43:49,000
♫ <i>Using this song, this song belongs to us</i> ♫

755
00:43:49,000 --> 00:43:52,600
♫ <i>Please don't cry again</i> ♫

756
00:43:52,600 --> 00:43:59,700
♫ <i>And don't ask when I'll return</i> ♫
